Movie: The Hunger Games: The Ballad of Songbirds & Snakes
Review: They picked the one girl in the coal town who listens to Evanescence to fight to the death assisted by the Draco Malfoy/slim shady of evil Riverdale High. This astounding prequel provides next to no information about what actually makes President Snow or the Hunger Games what they are even with a lengthy 2h45 run time. Also I refuse to believe that a goofy blonde teen came up with the idea of making the games a spectacle, like it’s supposed to be America in the future. Does no one remember ABC’s Wipeout???

Review: Accurate depiction of what it was like to grow up in Prussia under the Kaiser. Don’t ask what Burghermeister Meisterburgher was doing in Namibia 1904-1908.
Chimpanzee Politics: Power and Sex Among Apes (1982)
And what a mood it is.

The old world is dying. The new one struggles to be born. It is our responsibility to remake the world as the pieces crash around us. In the great fish’s guts resides the power of flight; eat them and soar.

Wow ugly and unsettling! This was put on in the kid’s room at every adult Christmas party I was taken to by my parents in the late Bush/early Obama era. Until this watch, I was unaware of how little happens and how no characters are given any personality except for the lurking and leering alleged train pedophile (alleged by me, I am alleging).
Moral of the story: you must cry havoc and let slip your smokin’ hot girlfriend. She will devour your enemies in a single gulp, lick her fingers, then order dessert.
